        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Generally guildies don't roll on anything in my guild.  You get awarded loot. For the most part loot goes to the the people that can make a big difference in a raid.  Since necros are hardly ever thought to make a huge difference you might find yourself on the short end of the loot stick.  Be that as it may there are a few choice items you can work towards that can really make a difference. The +100 HP items are some of them.  I would pick a few of them before the raids and simply drill it into your guilds head that these items are important to you.  Thats pretty much all you can do.</P><P>Daryth Shadowspawn<BR>Warlock of Stormhammer<BR>Dark Servant of Enrapture</P><P>"Its not your soul, you were just holding it for me."<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
