        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> My guild does all loot on a points system.  The more raids you go to, the more points you get.  The more points you have, the higher you can bid on an item you want.  Simple as that.  We do sometimes have special raids where the target is to get this person this loot.  But that is usually an epic raid anyway.  I think merit is gay with all the great all/all pieces that are out there now.  If you are smart you won't be bidding as many points as me for something that you wont be using very much.</P><P><P><img src="http://ddl.dyc.edu/~felix/tests/testuncool.jpg" border=0></P><BR><P><img src="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/jimicapone/pics/cutekid.bmp" border=0></P></P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
