        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=14211&TOPIC_ID=1943&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=High+end+HP+items%2C+should+necros+roll%3F&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Our guild is working on switching to some sort of raid point system.  Without going into great detail, the gist is that you save up raid points to bid on the items you really, really want.  This essentially (in theory) stops the scenerio where people roll on items just because their class can use it, or they want a new toy to play with, as opposed to rolling because it would really benefit them.</P><P>Honestly, there are problems involved with any system.  With merit, you have the pitfall of corruption and people playing favorites.  With a straight roll system, you can run into lootwhores rolling on shit they won't really put to use.</P><P>=-=-=-=-=-=-=<BR>Aildrik T'Quetzl<BR>"The more fear you make, the more loot you take"<BR>- Lex Luthar, Superman IV<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

